  "text": "The ConfigMap and Secret immutability feature in Kubernetes v1.32.0 is implemented across multiple components:\n\n**Field Definitions:**\nThe Immutable field is defined as a pointer to bool in:\n- kubernetes/kubernetes:staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/types.go (ConfigMap struct, line 7540; Secret struct, line 7397)\n- kubernetes/kubernetes:pkg/apis/core/types.go (internal API representations at lines 6281 and 6153)\n- kubernetes/api:core/v1/types.go (public API package)\n\n**Validation Logic (Immutable Field Validation & Mutation Prevention):**\nThe core validation and mutation prevention is implemented in kubernetes/kubernetes:pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go:\n- ValidateSecret (line 6764): Basic secret validation\n- ValidateSecretUpdate (line 6841): Prevents mutation of immutable secret data. When oldSecret.Immutable is true, it forbids changes to the immutable field itself (line 6847) and blocks any changes to the data field (line 6850).\n- ValidateConfigMap (line 6866): Basic configmap validation\n- ValidateConfigMapUpdate (line 6898): Prevents mutation of immutable configmap data. When oldCfg.Immutable is true, it forbids changes to the immutable field (line 6904), data field (line 6907), and binaryData field (line 6910).\n- ValidateImmutableField (line 363-364): Generic immutable field validation utility\n\n**Registry & Storage Strategy:**\nThe strategy files define how ConfigMaps and Secrets are created and updated:\n- kubernetes/kubernetes:pkg/registry/core/configmap/strategy.go: PrepareForUpdate and ValidateUpdate call the validation functions\n- kubernetes/kubernetes:pkg/registry/core/secret/strategy.go: PrepareForUpdate and ValidateUpdate call the validation functions\n- kubernetes/kubernetes:pkg/registry/core/configmap/storage/storage.go: REST storage layer using the strategy\n- kubernetes/kubernetes:pkg/registry/core/secret/storage/storage.go: REST storage layer using the strategy\n\n**Watch Optimization (Skipping Immutable Objects):**\nThe watch-based optimization is the key performance feature that stops watching immutable objects:\n- kubernetes/kubernetes:pkg/kubelet/util/manager/watch_based_manager.go (lines 333-348): In the Get method, when an object is retrieved, if c.isImmutable(object) returns true, the code calls item.setImmutable() and item.stop(), stopping the reflector watch. The isImmutableFunc type (line 44) is a callback that checks if an object is immutable.\n- kubernetes/kubernetes:pkg/kubelet/configmap/configmap_manager.go (lines 148-157): NewWatchingConfigMapManager creates an isImmutable closure that checks if configMap.Immutable != nil && *configMap.Immutable, then passes it to NewWatchBasedManager\n- kubernetes/kubernetes:pkg/kubelet/secret/secret_manager.go (lines 149-158): NewWatchingSecretManager creates an isImmutable closure that checks if secret.Immutable != nil && *secret.Immutable, then passes it to NewWatchBasedManager\n\n**Type Conversion:**\n- kubernetes/kubernetes:pkg/apis/core/v1/zz_generated.conversion.go: Handles conversion of the Immutable field between internal and v1 API versions\n\n**Client Configuration:**\n- kubernetes/client-go:applyconfigurations/core/v1/configmap.go: ConfigMapApplyConfiguration includes Immutable field (line 35) and WithImmutable method (line 248)\n- kubernetes/client-go:applyconfigurations/core/v1/secret.go: SecretApplyConfiguration includes Immutable field and WithImmutable method\n\n**Tests:**\n- kubernetes/kubernetes:pkg/kubelet/util/manager/watch_based_manager_test.go: Contains TestImmutableSecretStopsTheReflector (line 210) which tests that immutable secrets cause the reflector to stop\n- kubernetes/kubernetes:test/integration/kubelet/watch_manager_test.go: Integration tests for watch manager behavior with immutable objects\n\nThe feature prevents data mutations for immutable ConfigMaps and Secrets while optimizing kubelet watch performance by stopping reflectors for immutable objects, reducing unnecessary network and memory overhead."
}

